column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Used depth finder + took reading at 32'.  Partly cloudy + wind @ ~5 mph.
Temp. 48 degrees F- but warming.  Rained .5" Monday a.m.-today lake smooth as glass.  No one on lake except a pair of loons watching.  Water level Up ~3" from last check
Algae building up in deep area of lake.  Bright sunshine this a.m.
Not as much algae near surface as last check- partly cloudy but not as much smoke from forest fires in west blocking sun.  4 loons on lake.
Not a cloud in the sky- no wind- water like a glass.  Algae level high.  2 young loons + 1 adult on lake this a.m.
Partly cloudy- less algae in water.  Not as many people in cottages- will have to enjoy peace + quiet for another fall + winter.
Little windy.  Too cold to swim.  Has rained 6.1" past 3 days.
Too cold to swim. 36 degrees F this a.m.  A lot of foreign matter in water.  Received 9.1" rain during past 2.5 weeks.
Bright sun + water like sheet of glass.  One lonely teal feeding near shore.
Partly cloudy- but nice bright sun.
Too cold to swim.  Partly cloudy- lake relatively soon.
Water is cooling down.  Very few clouds- bright sunshine- wind calm to 5 mph gusts.  Have the lake to myself.
Too cold to swim.  Thin ice around shore line this a.m.  Maybe last check for this year - we'll see.
Water like glass this a.m. and bright sunshine.
Bright sun- loons on lake + 49 degrees F.
Beautiful warm day- heavy boat traffic-off on showers.
Algal bloom not apparent at this time.
Very little algae-first sunshine in days.
Clear- sunny aft.- very little algae.
43 degrees F- sunny- algae heavy in deep water.
Still have heavy algae in deep water- sunny + water calm- one pair of loons on lake.
Beautiful sunshine but too cold to swim.  Ice out on 5/14/96.  Seemed to be a lot of sediment in water.
Partly cloudy- 60 degrees- water starting to warm up. pair of loons on lake.
Algal bloom starting- sunny- warm- calm- 2 loons came up to boat.
Calm- partly cloudy- heavy algal bloom- 2 loons on lake.
Partly cloudy- light wind- heavy algae- 4 loons on lake - 2 old - 2 young.
Slightly overcast- light wind- pair of loons on lake (young ones) .
Mostly sunny- calm- 60 degrees F- lake level normal- algae heavy in deep water.
Sunny- light wind- algae heavy- lake level normal- one person fishing.
Heavy algal bloom- sunny- light wind- no loons on lake today.
Water riled up because of rain last night. algae bloom very heavy. partly sunny + warm.
Mostly sunny- calm- algae bloom still on heavy side.
Not a cloud in the sky- calm- very high level of algae. several flocks of geese moving south.
Partly cloudy- light wind- looks like lake is starting to turn over.
Mostly sunny- no wind on lake- best clarity since July. 39 degrees F.
Calm water. 90 degrees. lots of pine pollen on water
75 degrees. North wind at 5 MPH. Very clear water and no pollen. No one else on water.
70 degrees. South winds at 10 MPH. Partly cloudy. 2 adult loons with 2 chicks.
82 degrees. North wind at 5 MPH. Partly cloudy- very rainy weather.
70 degrees. Calm. SW wind 5-10 MPH. Clear sky. No rain for 5 days.
85 degrees. Clear and calm. Very humid. 1 other boat on lake. Stormed 2 days prior.
75 degrees. Partly cloudy. Just 3 loons on the lake.
75 degrees. Clear- west wind at 5 MPH. Rained hard last night.
cloudy- 5-10 mph winds from SW- only 1 other boat on the lake
partly cloudy- my wife and another couple aboard
partly cloudy - 2 other boats on the lake - wind from W ~ 5mph
partly cloudy- shared with a couple from Iowa. visited our family of 4 loons
very clear water- a bit of pine pokken on water- 75 degress- west winds 5 mph- 1 loon on water
little breeze- 87 degrees- 2 boats on water- went to check on 3 loons- slight tint to water
west wind @10 mph- visited the 3 loons with two friends
NW wind 5-10- had two friends and visited loons - sunny and 82 degrees
sunny- calm- 2 other boats on water- saw the 3 loons
Pine pollen has been falling- lots of yellow crap on water
Very hot the past 10 days (92 f today)
rained last night- very nice- partly cloudy- calm
Partly cloudy- N light winds- 77F- rain shower at 1:15PM
Partly cloudy- North light winds- 70F- saw 2 newborn loon chicks
Partly cloudy- SW winds 5-10 mph- 74F- loon chicks are growing fast
Partly cloudy - NW winds 5 to 10 - 75 degrees
60 degrees SW @ 5. Sunny - last 4 days was lot of wind and stormy. Water color tinted.
82 degrees. SW @ 7. Partly cloudy - has been hot and humid. Water color tinted.
Light NE winds- 1 loon to visit. Partly cloudy
